casebody.data:
STANSBURY, Etc. v. DIRECTOR OF PATUXENT INSTITUTION [App. No. 61,

September Term, 1962.]

Decided February 8, 1963.

Before Bruñe, C. J., and Henderson, Hammond, Horney and Marbury, JJ.

Per Curiam:.

In this application for leave to appeal from a finding of defective delinquency, the applicant states merely that he “disagrees with the decision of the Court.” Assuming, without deciding, that this statement is in compliance with Rule 894 a 2 (a), we have examined the report of Dr. Boslow and find the evidence legally sufficient to support the judgment.

Application denied.
